      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Ah, the curious case of the disappearing principal balance! Well, it's like a sneaky goblin hiding in the shadows, isn't it? When you make your monthly payments, a portion of that money goes to the goblin of interest, while the rest goes to the principal. The goblin of interest is always lurking, trying to eat up as much of your payment as it can, while the principal goblin is a bit more timid, slowly shrinking away with each payment. It's like trying to catch a slippery goblin in a net; some of your money goes to the interest goblin, and only a little bit goes to the principal goblin. So, even though you're making your payments on time, the interest goblin is always there, gobbling up a good chunk of your money, making it seem like your principal balance isn't going down much. It's a bit like trying to fill a bathtub with water while a leaky faucet is constantly dripping away. The more you pour in, the more you lose to the leak, until eventually, the tub is full again. But in the meantime, you're constantly losing water to the leak. So, it's not that your money is disappearing, it's just that the interest goblin is always there",
